<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="PeruTM6.10">
<l>alli malarttiru maṅkaikkēḷvaṉ ṟaṉṉai nayantiḷa vāyccimārkaḷ</l>
<l>ellip poḻutiṉi lēmattūṭi yeḷki yuraitta vuraiyataṉaik</l>
<l>kolli nakarkkiṟai kūṭaṟkōmāṉ kulacē karaṉiṉ ṉicaiyiṉmēvic</l>
<l>colliya viṉṟamiḻ mālaipattuñ collaval lārkkillai tuṉpantāṉē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>There will be no affliction for those who are capable of uttering</l>
<l>all ten [songs of] the garland in sweet Tamil,</l>
<l>that were uttered, joining [them] with sweet music,</l>
<l>by Kulacēkaraṉ, the chief of the Kolli city, the emperor of Kūṭal,</l>
<l>[who sang] the words spoken by the young cowherdesses desiring</l>
<l rend="indent">the Husband of the woman Śrī who is on the lotus blossom,</l>
<l rend="indent">having disparaged [Him and] sulked during the middle watch of the night time.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
